{"title":"Affordance Learning for End-to-End Visuomotor Robot Control","domain":"ROBOTICS","seeds":[{"problem":"End-to-end visuomotor policies typically require large amounts of task- and hardware-specific real data and struggle to generalize; training purely from RGB while keeping the representation interpretable and transferable is challenging.","method":"Introduce a modular, fully differentiable pipeline with three learned components trained solely on synthetic/simulation data: (1) a variational affordance encoder-decoder (VAED) that takes an RGB image and outputs both a pixel-wise affordance map and a low-dimensional latent affordance vector s; (2) a policy network that maps s concatenated with camera pose to a compact action latent a, trained in simulation with a supervised loss on the end-effector goal using differentiable forward kinematics (FK) to backpropagate through the FK computation; and (3) a trajectory VAE that decodes a into a full joint-space trajectory. Using VAEs enforces smooth, low-dimensional latent spaces for both perception and action, improving data efficiency. Composing the frozen perception and trajectory modules with the learned policy enables zero-shot sim-to-real transfer on a Franka Panda for a ball-in-container task and robustness under significant visual clutter."},{"problem":"Collecting pixel-wise affordance labels for training is labor-intensive and limits scalability and generalization across objects and scenes.","method":"Propose an automatic, domain-randomized data generation pipeline in Blender that renders paired RGB images and ground-truth affordance masks (e.g., wrap-grasp, contain) without any manual labeling. The pipeline randomizes cup shape, object/textures, camera pose, lighting, table/clutter (using YCB objects), producing a 1M-image dataset. Training VAED on this data yields an RGB-only affordance detector that transfers to real images and achieves competitive results on the UMD affordance benchmark, comparable to RGB-D baselines. Code for dataset generation and training is released (https://github.com/gamleksi/affordancegym)."}]}
